{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"e6cd4377-e7f6-4c3a-ae32-cb43deacd552","content":"","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01RUbWG7m2bTxg8uC8GTTGhG","name":"report_intent","arguments":{"intent":"Migrating xUnit v2 to v3"},"type":"function"},{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_017Y7iQBsrqAZN6JgxYouzzE","name":"web_fetch","arguments":{"url":"https://api.nuget.org/v3-flatcontainer/xunit.v3/index.json"},"type":"function","toolTitle":"Fetching web content","intentionSummary":"https://api.nuget.org/v3-flatcontainer/xunit.v3/index.json"}],"interactionId":"145c2187-e04e-4548-8075-6ceb0cd1966b","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"Now I understand the project. Let me migrate from xUnit.net v2 to v3:\n\n1. **`.csproj` changes:**\n   - Update `TargetFramework` from `net462` to a modern TFM (xUnit v3 requires at least `net472` for .NET Framework, or `net6.0`+). Since the project was targeting `net462`, I'll upgrade to `net8.0` which is the current LTS.\n   - Replace `xunit` v2 package with `xunit.v3` package\n   - Remove `xunit.runner.visualstudio` (v3 has its own runner built in)\n   - Drop `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk` since it's not needed for v3, and change the project SDK to `Microsoft.NET.Sdk` with `OutputType` set to `Exe` because xUnit v3 test projects are executables rather than class libraries.\n\n2. **`SampleTests.cs` changes:**\n   - The namespace and basic attributes like `[Fact]` and `Assert` remain the same, though I need to check what else changes in the test class structure for v3.\n\n3. **`global.json` changes:**\n   - The VSTest runner setting should be updated or removed since xUnit v3 uses Microsoft.Testing.Platform by default.\n\nNow I'm looking into the specific xUnit v3 migration requirements—the package name changes to `xunit.v3`, test projects become executables, and there's a minimum .NET version requirement.\n\nFor the target framework, xUnit v3 needs at least `net472` for .NET Framework or `net6.0` and above for .NET Core, so I should upgrade the old `net462` to `net8.0`. The namespaces and basic syntax like `[Fact]` and `Assert` remain unchanged, and the test runner is now built into the project itself.\n\nUpdating the project file... I need to verify the latest xUnit v3 version and determine the right configuration for the global.json file—for xUnit v3 executables, I should probably remove the test runner section entirely or update it to use Microsoft.Testing.Platform instead of VSTest.","outputTokens":1210,"requestId":"083A:1EA15F:D6EAAD:F90C21:69EAC873"},"id":"9f3c6afe-cd41-4b21-a89e-dbdfc2ccd566","timestamp":"2026-04-24T01:34:04.167Z","parentId":"5473cacb-77e4-4497-a657-e43df6cc27ea"}
